01:02.809 --> 01:03.506
Hey, Speedy.

01:03.549 --> 01:05.650
I'll have a couple of slices
of carrot pizza.

01:05.829 --> 01:08.098
Or you can have as many
slices as you want--

01:08.132 --> 01:11.376
at the buffet!
Six bucks, all you can eat.

01:11.653 --> 01:14.645
Oh, I like a buffet.

01:15.861 --> 01:17.362
What's, uh, going on?

01:17.396 --> 01:18.830
Sullivan's.

01:18.864 --> 01:19.930
What's Sullivan's?

01:19.964 --> 01:22.566
The new restaurant
across the street.

01:25.033 --> 01:26.871
I don't want them taking
any of my customers.

01:26.905 --> 01:29.508
I'm going to eat
all your profits.

01:29.543 --> 01:31.877
Bad business move, Speedy.

01:31.912 --> 01:34.515
Except for him.
They can have him.

01:34.549 --> 01:35.816
Come on, Bugs, check it out.

01:35.850 --> 01:38.919
And don't think I'm not
coming back for seconds.

01:38.954 --> 01:40.988
And thirds! And fourths!

01:41.022 --> 01:43.858
And fifths! [Chokes]

01:43.892 --> 01:45.526
[Coughing]

01:45.560 --> 01:48.429
Ok, we got the pepperoni,
we got the sausage,

01:48.463 --> 01:52.068
we got the classic cheese.
We got it all.

01:52.102 --> 01:54.104
We got the--ooh.

01:54.138 --> 01:57.475
Good thing you're not
the health department.

01:57.509 --> 02:00.845
They've been
on a roll offensively.

02:00.880 --> 02:02.547
Thompson with the jam.

02:02.582 --> 02:04.650
It's just so horrible.

02:04.684 --> 02:06.719
Me, almost choking.

02:06.754 --> 02:09.823
I know. Very scary.

02:09.857 --> 02:13.594
I mean, so, so horrible!

02:13.628 --> 02:14.695
[Buzzer on tv]
[Mutes TV]

02:14.730 --> 02:16.531
You want to talk
about it some more?

02:16.566 --> 02:21.136
No. I'm fine.
You watch your game.

02:21.937 --> 02:23.137
Since the all-star break--

02:23.172 --> 02:27.007
I mean, it's just that you realize

02:27.041 --> 02:30.578
how fragile life is.

02:31.213 --> 02:33.180
...from the three point line.

02:33.215 --> 02:36.751
It can just turn, in a second!

02:36.786 --> 02:39.221
[Mutes TV]

02:39.255 --> 02:41.590
A second.

02:45.128 --> 02:46.261
So horrible.

02:46.295 --> 02:49.097
I think if they score here--

02:49.131 --> 02:51.032
Do you need to talk?

02:51.067 --> 02:52.567
No. No.

02:52.601 --> 02:54.669
Keep watching.

02:55.605 --> 02:58.306
I'm going to learn
to play the piano!

02:58.341 --> 02:59.207
What?

02:59.242 --> 03:01.643
My whole life
I've wanted to play piano,

03:01.678 --> 03:03.979
but I always said, tomorrow.

03:04.013 --> 03:05.481
I'll learn tomorrow.

03:05.515 --> 03:09.419
Well, guess what.
Tomorrow isn't promised to you!

03:09.453 --> 03:12.556
All you have is today.

03:12.590 --> 03:15.492
Why piano?

03:15.527 --> 03:16.794
My grand mummy played.

03:16.828 --> 03:20.331
I distinctly remember
listening by her side

03:20.366 --> 03:23.334
as she tickled the ivories.

03:23.369 --> 03:25.270
I would dance
as she filled the room

03:25.304 --> 03:29.641
with the sounds of Chopin,
Bach, Jerry Lee Lewis.

03:29.676 --> 03:31.810
She offered
to teach me many times,

03:31.845 --> 03:34.880
but my answer
was always the same--

03:34.915 --> 03:36.582
tomorrow, grand mummy.

03:36.617 --> 03:40.153
I'll learn to play tomorrow.

03:42.090 --> 03:46.693
So now do you see why I must
learn to play the piano?

03:46.728 --> 03:48.262
Ehh, not really.

03:48.296 --> 03:49.797
But whatever floats your boat.

03:49.831 --> 03:54.535
Then it's settled. Tomorrow
I will learn to play piano.

03:54.569 --> 03:55.769
Don't you mean today?

03:55.804 --> 03:59.140
Nah, it's kind of late,
it's almost dinner time.

03:59.174 --> 04:00.341
Oh, I'm starving.

04:00.375 --> 04:03.745
I didn't eat that much
after I choked.

04:09.518 --> 04:13.220
- Where's the TV?
- In here, boys!

04:14.155 --> 04:16.390
Daffy, where's the TV?

04:16.423 --> 04:19.358
I sold it.
Put her upstairs, boys.

04:19.394 --> 04:20.927
First bedroom on the right.

04:20.962 --> 04:22.762
What do you mean, you sold it?!

04:22.797 --> 04:25.832
To buy a piano.
We talked about this.

04:25.866 --> 04:27.100
No, we didn't!

04:27.134 --> 04:28.801
Well, no, not explicitly.

04:28.835 --> 04:30.235
But yesterday's conversation

04:30.270 --> 04:33.239
was riddled
with undertones and innuendos.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.040
You said,
whatever floats your boat.

04:35.075 --> 04:38.677
And selling your TV to buy
myself a piano floats my boat.

04:38.712 --> 04:41.581
But I guess what
you're really saying is,

04:41.615 --> 04:44.150
you want to sink my boat.

04:44.184 --> 04:45.151
You hear that, boys?

04:45.186 --> 04:48.922
Looks like the "S.S. Daffy Duck"
is going down.

04:48.956 --> 04:50.524
Take her away, boys.

04:50.558 --> 04:54.762
I should have just died
choking on that pizza.

04:54.796 --> 04:56.330
You hear that, boys?

04:56.364 --> 04:58.866
I should have just died.

04:58.901 --> 05:01.369
Fine. Keep the piano.

05:01.403 --> 05:05.239
You hear that, boys?!
The piano stays.

05:05.273 --> 05:07.672
You're not going to regret this.

05:07.706 --> 05:11.141
Soon you'll be the one
dancing beside the piano

05:11.176 --> 05:14.611
as I fill our home
with the sounds of Beethoven,

05:14.646 --> 05:17.814
Rachmaninoff,
and Bruce Hornsby.

05:17.848 --> 05:20.016
So much Bruce Hornsby.

05:20.050 --> 05:23.853
That'll be all, boys.

05:23.887 --> 05:25.520
[Groaning]

05:25.555 --> 05:28.623
Why are the boys
still standing there?

05:28.657 --> 05:30.425
You got to tip 'em.

05:30.459 --> 05:31.492
I'm kind of tapped out.

05:31.527 --> 05:35.095
I didn't get
that much for your TV.

05:39.864 --> 05:42.927
[Clearing throat]

05:45.263 --> 05:48.098
Whoa, listen to this sucker!

05:48.133 --> 05:52.635
This plays so much louder
than my grandmother's!

05:53.537 --> 05:55.938
I'm going to go buy a new TV.

05:55.972 --> 05:57.272
What?

05:57.307 --> 05:59.741
I'm going to buy a new TV.

05:59.776 --> 06:01.443
I can't hear you!

06:01.477 --> 06:03.411
Because
you're playing too loud!

06:03.445 --> 06:09.182
You're right!
Grand mummy would be proud.

06:15.678 --> 06:18.208
Alright, your TV
will be delivered next week.

06:18.448 --> 06:19.569
Can I get you anything else?

06:19.583 --> 06:22.219
Nah. I think I'm...
What are those?

06:22.253 --> 06:23.987
Noise canceling headphones.
They're great.

06:24.022 --> 06:26.524
You can't even see them
and they block out all sound.

06:26.559 --> 06:31.529
All sound, huh?
I'll take 'em.

06:31.564 --> 06:32.530
Speedy?

06:32.565 --> 06:35.200
- Oh, hey, senor Bugs.
- What are you doing here?

06:35.235 --> 06:37.032
Buying a bunch
of flat screen TVs.

06:37.152 --> 06:39.071
Sullivan's, man,
they're killing me.

06:39.105 --> 06:40.839
They've always got
the big game on.

06:40.874 --> 06:42.942
You got to keep up
with the Jonas'.

06:42.976 --> 06:44.610
- Who?
- The Jonas'.

06:44.644 --> 06:47.546
- You know, the competition.
- The Joneses.

06:47.580 --> 06:49.648
That's what I said.

06:51.451 --> 06:54.820
[Playing tune on piano]

07:07.433 --> 07:11.402
You're a natural piano player.

07:11.436 --> 07:12.570
Do you mind?

07:12.604 --> 07:17.975
I told you I'd give you
your lesson when she's done.

07:21.579 --> 07:25.149
Very good, Winnie.

07:25.183 --> 07:27.584
Ohh.

07:27.619 --> 07:31.521
I'll see you next week.

07:31.556 --> 07:34.591
So is this your first
piano lesson?

07:34.626 --> 07:37.494
Yep. And I want you to be
harsh. No sugar coating.

07:37.528 --> 07:41.064
I don't want you to baby me
like you did that little girl.

07:41.099 --> 07:44.034
I'm not here to get
a stupid gold star.

07:44.069 --> 07:46.337
I'm here to play. You got it?

07:46.371 --> 07:47.404
No coddling.

07:47.439 --> 07:53.010
Ok! Let's begin with
"The Grand Old Duke of York."

07:53.045 --> 07:56.047
[Playing tune]

08:00.019 --> 08:03.288
[Daffy playing out of tune]

08:04.324 --> 08:07.893
No, that wasn't quite right.

08:07.927 --> 08:09.995
Good lord,
do you have to be so harsh?!

08:10.029 --> 08:13.198
This is my first lesson!
I'm like a baby!

08:13.233 --> 08:14.667
You have to coddle me.

08:14.701 --> 08:18.504
Ok. Let's try again.

08:18.539 --> 08:21.140
[Playing tune]

08:25.412 --> 08:28.881
[Daffy playing out of tune]

08:31.785 --> 08:33.653
[Thud]

08:33.687 --> 08:36.755
Do I get a gold star?

08:38.491 --> 08:40.125
[Door opens]

08:40.159 --> 08:41.726
How was your first lesson?

08:41.760 --> 08:45.764
Ugh. My teacher
is very, very tough.

08:45.798 --> 08:47.766
And mean. And unforgiving.

08:47.800 --> 08:51.269
But she's easy on the eyes,
I'll give her that.

08:51.303 --> 08:52.170
Ohh.

08:52.204 --> 08:54.573
So does that mean
you'll be playing piano

08:54.607 --> 08:55.807
over there from now on?

08:55.841 --> 08:58.276
No way!
The only way to get better

08:58.310 --> 08:59.511
is to practice at home.

08:59.545 --> 09:02.013
And since I have no job
and acute insomnia,

09:02.048 --> 09:05.583
I can practice 24 hours a day!

09:07.319 --> 09:11.055
[Daffy playing piano
out of tune]

09:14.559 --> 09:17.294
[No audio]

09:20.565 --> 09:21.732
[No audio]

09:21.767 --> 09:24.902
...five minutes! What in
tarnation is he doing up there?!

09:24.936 --> 09:29.841
Sounds like he's throwing a bunch of
church bells down an elevator shaft!

09:29.875 --> 09:32.343
Oh. Daffy's learning
to play piano.

09:32.378 --> 09:33.678
Well, it's too dang loud.

09:33.713 --> 09:37.849
It's 10:00 at night. Some of us
have got work in the morning.

09:37.884 --> 09:40.351
Well, not me, but if I did,

09:40.386 --> 09:42.087
I bet my work performance
would suffer

09:42.121 --> 09:44.456
and I'd nod off in the middle
of a big meeting

09:44.490 --> 09:47.092
due to the fact that I got
no sleep the night before

09:47.126 --> 09:50.962
'cause of that butchering
of "The Grand Old Duke of York."

09:50.996 --> 09:53.931
- Anything else?
- As a matter of fact, yes.

09:53.966 --> 09:57.736
I got a long list
of grievances with you two.

09:57.770 --> 10:02.207
For starters, your sprinklers
spray in front of my mailbox...

10:02.241 --> 10:04.209
[No audio]

10:04.243 --> 10:05.376
Uh-huh.

10:05.411 --> 10:09.748
Also unrelated, your dumb
dog's got a barking problem.

10:09.782 --> 10:11.650
He don't ever shut up!

10:11.685 --> 10:12.685
All I hear is,

10:12.719 --> 10:14.153
- woof, woof, woof.
- Uh-huh.

10:14.188 --> 10:18.659
Actually, it's more like a...
[Imitating Tasmanian Devil]

10:19.661 --> 10:22.029
- Uh-huh.
- Also, I want to talk

10:22.063 --> 10:23.297
about that parade float.

10:23.331 --> 10:26.433
Half the time he parks it
in front of my driveway.

10:26.468 --> 10:29.003
And if I got to be somewhere--
which I never do--

10:29.037 --> 10:32.540
but if I did,
I'd not be able to get there,

10:32.574 --> 10:34.575
wherever "there" is!

10:34.609 --> 10:36.076
I know what you mean.

10:36.111 --> 10:38.779
You do? You really do?

10:38.813 --> 10:40.647
- Uh-huh.
- Wow.

10:40.682 --> 10:42.549
Thanks for listening, rabbit.

10:42.583 --> 10:43.917
I feel a lot better.

10:43.952 --> 10:47.587
Well, this is the best
conversation we ever had.

10:47.621 --> 10:50.089
Oh, let the kid play piana.

10:50.124 --> 10:51.857
I wish I'd learned myself.

10:51.892 --> 10:55.328
You, you have a good night.

10:55.362 --> 10:58.330
[Piano playing continues]

10:58.365 --> 11:01.801
You have a blessed evening.

11:03.437 --> 11:05.004
Did you hear me play?!

11:05.039 --> 11:07.874
Oh, yeah. "Grand Old Duke of York," right?

11:07.909 --> 11:10.143
[Gasps] You recognized it.

11:10.178 --> 11:11.512
I am getting better!

11:11.546 --> 11:15.316
[Daffy playing piano
out of tune]

11:17.353 --> 11:20.355
I'm telling you. They're the
greatest things in the world.

11:20.389 --> 11:23.191
Daffy's piano playing
is that bad, huh?

11:23.226 --> 11:24.526
They don't just work on Daffy.

11:24.561 --> 11:26.961
They work on all sorts
of annoying people.

11:26.996 --> 11:29.898
I had a ten minute conversation
with Yosemite Sam

11:29.932 --> 11:32.133
and I didn't have
to listen to a word of it.

11:32.168 --> 11:34.369
Isn't that a little rude?

11:34.403 --> 11:35.603
No way!

11:35.638 --> 11:37.739
I was more rude
before I got these.

11:37.773 --> 11:39.707
You know what it's like
talking to me.

11:39.742 --> 11:43.744
I'm always rolling my eyes,
saying something sarcastic.

11:43.778 --> 11:47.281
Not anymore.
Now I just pop these babies in.

11:47.315 --> 11:48.482
Can't people tell?

11:48.516 --> 11:51.051
Nah, I just nod a lot, you
know, throw in a few uh-huhs,

11:51.085 --> 11:53.053
and when it looks like
they're wrapping it up,

11:53.088 --> 11:55.155
you know, I just say,
"I know what you mean."

11:55.189 --> 11:56.956
I'm actually
a pretty great listener,

11:56.991 --> 11:59.071
as long as I don't have
to hear what anyone's saying.

11:59.093 --> 12:02.512
Have you, uh, ever used
those things on me?

12:02.632 --> 12:04.963
What?! No!

12:04.998 --> 12:07.298
So yesterday
when I was telling you

12:07.333 --> 12:09.667
about that recurring dream
I've been having,

12:09.702 --> 12:11.172
you were listening?

12:11.292 --> 12:13.052
To every word.

12:13.172 --> 12:15.239
Phew! Ok, good.

12:15.273 --> 12:17.474
Because I had it again
last night!

12:17.509 --> 12:19.076
It's the strangest thing.

12:19.110 --> 12:22.513
It's like, I'm in my house,
but I'm not in my house.

12:22.548 --> 12:25.383
And it's like everything's
in black and white.

12:25.417 --> 12:29.277
And I can smell someone making
breakfast, like buttered toast,

12:29.397 --> 12:32.724
but then I go into the kitchen
and no one's there.

12:32.759 --> 12:34.092
Uh-huh.

12:34.127 --> 12:37.163
I mean, I feel like the dream has
something to do with my mother.

12:37.197 --> 12:39.632
Or maybe my sister.
Whatever the case,

12:39.666 --> 12:41.500
it's very unsettling.

12:41.535 --> 12:43.069
I know what you mean.

12:43.373 --> 12:45.544
Thanks, Bugs.

12:45.664 --> 12:47.773
You going to eat that?

12:47.808 --> 12:50.676
- Uh-huh.
- Oh, ok.

12:50.711 --> 12:53.112
Sorry.

12:56.000 --> 12:57.952
Oh, no.

12:58.661 --> 12:59.698
No.

13:02.255 --> 13:03.275
No.

13:03.870 --> 13:06.372
Here, let's try it together.

13:06.406 --> 13:09.808
[Playing
"Grand Old Duke of York"]

13:23.757 --> 13:26.926
["Grand Old Duke of York"
continues]

13:37.437 --> 13:39.972
[No audio]

13:57.123 --> 13:59.858
[Playing out of tune]

14:03.129 --> 14:04.296
Well?

14:04.330 --> 14:08.133
Do I finally get a gold star?

14:08.167 --> 14:09.200
[Door opens]

14:09.235 --> 14:12.108
Unbelievable!
Just unbelievable.

14:12.228 --> 14:13.366
Ughh.

14:15.808 --> 14:20.211
I've been practicing forever
and I'm still not any better.

14:20.245 --> 14:21.912
What is wrong with me?

14:21.947 --> 14:25.249
What do you think?
I need you to be honest.

14:25.283 --> 14:28.385
I want the truth.
Don't hold back.

14:28.420 --> 14:31.088
Do you think I should
quit piano?

14:31.122 --> 14:32.623
- Uh-huh.
- I knew it!

14:32.657 --> 14:34.973
This whole thing's been
a giant waste of time.

14:35.093 --> 14:37.960
And it's proof that I should
never try anything again. Ever.

14:38.080 --> 14:41.965
Because I will fail.
I fail at everything.

14:42.000 --> 14:43.433
Uh-huh.

14:43.468 --> 14:44.301
So why try?

14:44.336 --> 14:46.036
I just shouldn't ever try,
right?

14:46.071 --> 14:48.672
Because when you try,
you expose yourself

14:48.707 --> 14:51.108
to the possibility of failure.

14:51.142 --> 14:52.576
And there's no point in trying

14:52.610 --> 14:55.011
if there's a chance
that you might fail.

14:55.046 --> 14:56.746
You know what I mean?

14:56.781 --> 14:58.581
I know what you mean.

14:58.616 --> 15:00.778
Thanks, Bugs.

15:08.825 --> 15:12.594
Pretty classy, huh?

15:16.403 --> 15:18.303
Speedy, what is all this?

15:18.337 --> 15:20.972
It's called fine dining.
Like at Sullivan's.

15:21.007 --> 15:24.610
Shrimp scampi?
Ooh, that sounds good.

15:24.644 --> 15:26.812
Then again,
I've never had it before

15:26.846 --> 15:29.649
and there's no point
in trying something new.

15:29.683 --> 15:30.683
Right, Bugs?

15:30.717 --> 15:34.587
I guess I'll just
get the buffet.

15:36.990 --> 15:37.923
[Indistinct chatter]

15:37.958 --> 15:40.860
You messed with
the wrong mouse, Sullivan's.

15:41.562 --> 15:44.631
Uh, they didn't mess
with you, Speedy.

15:44.665 --> 15:46.599
It's just another restaurant.

15:46.634 --> 15:47.834
It's my competitive nature.

15:47.868 --> 15:49.936
How did you think
I became the fastest mouse

15:49.970 --> 15:51.071
in all of Mexico? No.

15:51.105 --> 15:53.807
If Sullivan's has a buffet,
I got a buffet.

15:53.841 --> 15:56.276
If Sullivan's has shrimp scampi,
I got shrimp scampi.

15:56.310 --> 15:58.545
If Sullivan's has live music
every Friday night,

15:58.579 --> 16:02.315
I got live music
every Friday night.

16:03.417 --> 16:05.184
You've got live music tonight?

16:05.219 --> 16:06.919
Huh? What are you
talking about?

16:06.954 --> 16:09.389
- You're the one who arranged it!
- What?

16:09.423 --> 16:10.723
Please tell me this is a joke.

16:10.758 --> 16:13.393
You said you were going
to take care of everything.

16:13.427 --> 16:15.128
When did I say that?

16:15.162 --> 16:16.329
I asked you the other day.

16:16.363 --> 16:18.331
I said, I have a big favor
to ask you, and you can say no,

16:18.365 --> 16:22.502
but do you know of anyone who might be
available to perform on Friday night?

16:22.536 --> 16:23.737
And you said, uh-huh.

16:23.771 --> 16:25.071
And then I said, are you sure?

16:25.106 --> 16:28.307
And you said, uh-huh.
Then I said, thank you so much.

16:28.342 --> 16:30.076
This is such a nice gesture.

16:30.110 --> 16:31.610
You are a prince among men.

16:31.644 --> 16:33.045
And you said,
I know what you mean.

16:33.079 --> 16:34.980
Personally, I thought
that was a little bit boastful,

16:35.014 --> 16:38.317
but I'm not in a position
to judge, so I said, whatever.

16:38.351 --> 16:39.918
And here we are.

16:39.953 --> 16:41.887
Ehh, hypothetically,

16:41.921 --> 16:43.355
just throwing this out there,

16:43.390 --> 16:46.825
um, what would happen if,
for some reason,

16:46.860 --> 16:49.228
there was no live
entertainment tonight?

16:49.262 --> 16:52.331
Oh, not much.
Other than I will have wasted

16:52.366 --> 16:54.200
$500 on a full page ad.

16:54.235 --> 16:57.236
And all of these people will no
longer be customers of mine.

16:57.271 --> 16:59.605
They'll be customers
of Sullivan's!

16:59.640 --> 17:03.609
So please tell me
you got someone.

17:05.511 --> 17:09.047
- I got someone.
- You better.

17:10.883 --> 17:13.084
I've got great news!

17:13.118 --> 17:15.319
You're playing
the piano tonight.

17:15.354 --> 17:18.289
Me? I don't play piano.

17:18.323 --> 17:19.890
What are you talking about?

17:19.925 --> 17:21.224
What are you talking about?

17:21.260 --> 17:25.262
I asked you if I should quit,
and you said, uh-huh.

17:25.297 --> 17:28.132
Oh, boy. Ok,
forget our conversation.

17:28.165 --> 17:30.067
Even the part about
never trying anything

17:30.102 --> 17:34.038
if there's even the slightest
chance that you might fail?

17:34.072 --> 17:35.273
Especially that part!

17:35.307 --> 17:38.143
That's the worst advice
that anybody could ever give.

17:38.177 --> 17:42.314
Daffy, you said you wanted
to learn how to play the piano.

17:42.348 --> 17:43.508
So you have to stick with it,

17:43.516 --> 17:47.919
no matter how hard it is,
or how bad it sounds.

17:47.954 --> 17:49.822
You can do it.

17:49.856 --> 17:52.091
You really believe in me?

17:52.125 --> 17:55.161
Uh-huh. I mean, yes.

17:56.096 --> 17:59.099
[Piano playing]

17:59.133 --> 18:01.134
Thanks, Bugs.

18:01.168 --> 18:03.369
Don't thank me.
Thank Daffy.

18:03.403 --> 18:06.572
Don't thank me. Thank
Winnie Yang and her parents

18:06.607 --> 18:09.442
for letting her stay up so late.

18:24.892 --> 18:27.894
Eeh! You scared me to death.

18:27.929 --> 18:30.097
That's precisely what I want
to talk to you about.

18:30.131 --> 18:34.101
Choking on that pizza has really
made me think about things,

18:34.136 --> 18:39.740
specifically the arrangements
in the event of my...passing.

18:39.774 --> 18:40.808
What?!

18:40.842 --> 18:44.445
♪ Lay me to rest
inside a Corvette ♪

18:44.479 --> 18:49.283
♪ with a trunk full of yogurt
for the afterlife ♪

18:49.317 --> 18:53.887
♪ pull the Corvette
with a team of Clydesdales ♪

18:53.921 --> 18:59.192
♪ make sure that Tina
is there by my side ♪

18:59.227 --> 19:00.457
What if she's not dead?

19:00.577 --> 19:01.656
Just make it work.

19:01.776 --> 19:04.432
♪ For my eulogy ♪

19:04.466 --> 19:06.233
♪ get Neil Diamond to sing ♪

19:06.268 --> 19:11.273
♪ and use lots of quotes
from "Lord of the Rings" ♪

19:11.307 --> 19:15.277
♪ in lieu of flowers,
buy some raw meat ♪

19:15.312 --> 19:21.717
♪ then pay some pirates
to dance in the street ♪

19:21.751 --> 19:22.651
What?!

19:22.685 --> 19:26.154
♪ And the party will rage
for 900 days ♪

19:26.189 --> 19:30.459
♪ with bonfires and swearing
and random gun play ♪

19:30.493 --> 19:33.996
♪ and plaster the town
with photos of me ♪

19:34.030 --> 19:38.400
♪ this is my decree,
it's my legacy ♪

19:38.435 --> 19:41.937
♪ cryogenically
freeze my brain ♪

19:41.972 --> 19:45.408
♪ so the scientists can tinker ♪

19:45.442 --> 19:48.745
♪ think of the knowledge
that they'd retain ♪

19:48.779 --> 19:53.183
♪ from one of the world's
great thinkers ♪

19:53.218 --> 19:57.021
♪ it's a trifecta,
can't you see ♪

19:57.055 --> 20:02.193
♪ it's me, Da Vinci
and Socrates ♪

20:02.227 --> 20:04.595
Are we still talking
about your memorial?

20:04.629 --> 20:08.232
Yep.
♪ All the kids must attend ♪

20:08.266 --> 20:10.167
♪ Daffy Duck High ♪

20:10.201 --> 20:13.970
♪ and train as brick masons
and twirlers and spies ♪

20:14.005 --> 20:17.074
♪ though some should be ninjas
that do awesome stunts ♪

20:17.108 --> 20:22.746
♪ they'd all wear black robes
with my face on the front ♪

20:22.781 --> 20:26.618
♪ the 50 yard line
at the rose ball works great ♪

20:26.652 --> 20:31.356
♪ for my huge marble statue
with a big gold nameplate ♪

20:31.390 --> 20:33.425
♪ or under the sphinx ♪

20:33.459 --> 20:35.060
♪ or up here a mid ♪

20:35.094 --> 20:38.830
♪ but right at the top,
just open the lid ♪

20:38.864 --> 20:42.433
♪ and the party will rage
for 900 days ♪

20:42.467 --> 20:46.203
♪ with bonfires and swearing
and random gun play ♪

20:46.238 --> 20:50.074
♪ and plaster the town
with photos of me ♪

20:50.108 --> 20:53.744
♪ this is my decree,
it's my legacy ♪

20:53.778 --> 21:02.753
♪ this is my decree,
it's my legacy ♪

21:02.787 --> 21:04.414
So, what do you say?

21:04.534 --> 21:05.957
Why wait?

21:05.991 --> 21:08.119
What are you doing? Not now!

21:08.239 --> 21:10.062
The future!

21:10.096 --> 21:13.799
Way off in the future.

21:14.668 --> 21:18.638
[Daffy playing piano
out of tune]

21:37.723 --> 21:39.725
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

21:39.759 --> 21:41.782
I finally got a gold star!

21:41.903 --> 21:43.103
I did it! I did it!

21:43.138 --> 21:45.172
I did it, I did it, I did it!

21:45.207 --> 21:46.707
[Opens and closes door]

21:46.742 --> 21:50.210
Oh, ha, I've got
to remember to thank Bugs

21:50.245 --> 21:52.224
for giving me these.

